<h1>Privacy Policy for iVacuum</h1>
<p class="updated">Last updated: [INSERT DATE]</p>

<p>iVacuum ("the App") is built to free up storage space on your device by
compressing your photos and videos. This policy explains what data the App
accesses, what it does with that data, and what it never does.</p>

<h2>What the App Accesses</h2>
<p>iVacuum requests access to your device's photo and video library
(Photos app) so it can:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Scan your existing photos and videos to calculate their current file
  sizes</li>
  <li>Compress selected photos and videos when you choose to do so</li>
  <li>Save the compressed versions back to your photo library, replacing
  the originals</li>
</ul>

<h2>What Happens On Your Device</h2>
<p>All scanning and compression happens locally, on your device. Your
photos and videos are <strong>not</strong> uploaded to any server, sent to
any third party, or stored anywhere outside your device as part of this
process.</p>

<h2>Data We Do Not Collect</h2>
<p>iVacuum does not collect, store, or transmit:</p>
<ul>
  <li>The content of your photos or videos</li>
  <li>Your name, email, or contact information (beyond what's needed for
  in-app purchase processing, handled entirely by Apple — see below)</li>
  <li>Your location</li>
  <li>Browsing or usage data for advertising purposes</li>
</ul>

<h2>In-App Purchases</h2>
<p>iVacuum offers a one-time purchase to unlock full use of the App. This
purchase is processed entirely by Apple through the App Store's standard
in-app purchase system. iVacuum does not receive, store, or have access to
your payment information — that is handled solely by Apple in accordance
with <a href="https://www.apple.com/legal/privacy/">Apple's own Privacy
Policy</a>.</p>

<h2>Local Storage on Your Device</h2>
<p>The App keeps a small record on your device (not sent anywhere) of:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Whether you have agreed to the App's terms</li>
  <li>Whether you have purchased the lifetime unlock</li>
  <li>Which files have already been compressed, so they aren't processed
  again unnecessarily</li>
</ul>
<p>This information stays on your device and can be cleared by deleting
the App.</p>

<h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
<p>iVacuum does not integrate any third-party analytics, advertising, or
tracking services.</p>

<h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
<p>iVacuum is not directed at children and does not knowingly collect any
information from children.</p>

<h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
<p>If this policy changes, the updated version will be posted at this same
URL with a revised "Last updated" date above.</p>

<h2>Contact</h2>
<p>If you have questions about this policy, contact: <strong>[INSERT YOUR
EMAIL ADDRESS]</strong></p>

